  "biographies": [
    {
      "text": "Bibi Blocksberg is the leading character in a popular German radio series for children, which was later adapted into an animated television series. Bibi Blocksberg is a high-spirited 13-year-old girl who also happens to be a witch, inheriting her powers from her mother. Bibi enjoys using her magical abilities to pull pranks on grownups, particularly the principal of her school and the mayor of her hometown, though her tricks sometimes backfire and she has to use the same powers to put things right. Originally titled Eene Meene Hexerei, the radio series was renamed Bibi Blocksberg beginning with the eighth episode. Voiced by actress Susanna Bonasewicz (Katja Nottke provided Bibi's voice in three early episodes), Bibi Blocksberg debuted in 1980 and was still airing in 2010, with over 100 radio shows and 26 television episodes broadcast. Owing to the continued popularity of the Bibi Blocksberg series, nearly all the episodes of the radio show have been released on CD in Germany. ~ Mark Deming, Rovi",
      "portraits": []
    }
